title: Pumpkin Pie Cupcakes
directions: Mix together the pumpkin purée, sugars, eggs, vanilla and evaporated milk in a large bowl and mix using a hand or stand mixer until well combined.
Mix in the flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and salt until well mixed.
Line a cupcake pan with silicone cupcake liners or just spray the pan if you don’t have those.
Pour the batter in the silicone cupcake liners filling ½ full and bake in a preheated oven to 350° for 20 minutes.
Let the cupcakes cool before placing them in the fridge for 30 minutes.
